{{Infobox software | name = Virastyar | logo = Virastyar Logo.png | screenshot = | caption = | developer = Omid Kashefi<ref name="sf-v" /> | released = {{Start date and age|2011|02|02}} | latest release version = 3.5 | latest release date = {{Start date and age|2015|08|15}}<ref name="sf-v" /> | latest preview version = 4.0 Beta | latest preview date = {{Start date and age|2015|08|29}}<ref name="sf-v" /> | programming language = [[C Sharp (programming language)|C#]], [[Visual Basic for Applications]]<ref name="sf-v" /> | operating system = [[Windows]] | platform = [[Microsoft Word]], [[.NET Framework]], [[Visual Studio Tools for Applications]] | size = 59.1 [[Megabyte|MB]]<ref name="sf-v" /> | language = [[Persian language|Persian]] | genre = [[Spell checker]], [[plug-in (computing)|plug-in]] | license = [[GNU General Public License]] | website = {{URL|virastyar.ir}} }}
'''Virastyar''' ({{lang-fa| ویراستیار}}, meaning "editing assistant") is a [[Persian language|Persian]] [[Plug-in (computing)|add-in]] for [[Microsoft Word]] that performs Persian [[spell checking]], character standardization, [[Fingilish|Pinglish]] [[transliteration]], punctuation correction and calendar conversion.<ref>[http://www.virastyar.ir/?q=node/11 What is Virastyar?]</ref> It can conjugate approximately 46,000 simple verb tense and use inflection and morphological rules to recognize possible extensions of a word.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mehrnews.com/fa/newsdetail.aspx?NewsID=1232528 |title=Free Version of Persian Spell Checker is Released |date=May 11, 2010 |publisher=MehrNews|accessdate=Feb 28, 2011}}</ref> It covers approximately 2,800 non-verbal inflections for nouns, adjectives, adverbs, prepositions, numerals, classifiers, and pronouns.<ref>{{cite book |title= Towards Automatic Persian Spell Checker|last= Kashefi|first= Omid|year=2010|first2=Mitra |last2=Nasri |first3=Kamiar |last3=Kanani |first4=Mehrdad |last4=Senobari |first5=Sina |last5=Iravanian|first6=Alireza |last6=Dehlaghi-Ghadim |publisher=[[Supreme Council of ICT of Iran]] |location=Tehran, Iran |isbn=978-964-884-634-8 }}</ref>
Virastyar is mostly coded in [[C Sharp (programming language)|Microsoft Visual C#]] using [[.NET Framework]] and is a [[free software]], released under the [[GNU General Public License]].<ref name="sf-v">[http://sourceforge.net/projects/virastyar/ Virastyar at sourceforge.net]</ref>
